<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The OS_strnlen implementation calls memchr(s, 0, maxlen) which can read up to maxlen bytes starting at s. If a caller passes a maxlen that is larger than the actual size of the object pointed to by s (for example: OS_strnlen(&local->system_mountpt[10], sizeof(local->system_mountpt)) or OS_strnlen(some_pointer_into_buffer, sizeof(buffer))), memchr may access beyond the bounds of the underlying object and thus violate MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>
